2.Control: existing businesses, business reviews, new businesses, products or initiatives, and acquisitions and alliances
  a.define the different forms of liquidity risk to which they are exposed and where they fit in their enterprise risk universe
  b.communicate across their groups so that a common understanding is applied when evaluate and identify liquidity risk
  2.1 functions in charge of liquidity risk management
    its primary goal is to ensure funding is never at risk and the overall assets and liabilities are matched
